{
  "local_port": 33546,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some of the cool features on Google now?",
  "response": "Google Now, now known as Google Assistant, has evolved and integrated several cool features over time. Here are some of the most interesting and useful features available as of my last update:\n\n1. **Voice Commands and Conversational Interaction**:\n   - Google Assistant can understand and respond to natural language, allowing for more conversational interactions. You can ask follow-up questions without repeating the context.\n\n2. **Smart Home Control**:\n   - You can control smart home devices like lights, thermostats, and security systems with voice commands. This makes managing your home environment easier and more convenient.\n\n3. **Personalized Routines**:\n   - You can set up routines that trigger a series of actions with a single command. For example, saying \"Good morning\" could turn on the lights, start the coffee maker, and give you a weather update.\n\n4. **Continued Conversation**:\n   - Google Assistant can keep the conversation going without needing to repeat the wake word (\"Hey Google\") for each command, making interactions feel more natural.\n\n5. **Google Duplex**:\n   - This feature allows Google Assistant to make phone calls on your behalf to book reservations, schedule appointments, and more. It uses natural-sounding speech and can handle complex interactions.\n\n6. **Interpreter Mode**:\n   - Google Assistant can translate conversations in real-time, making it useful for travelers or anyone needing to communicate across language barriers.\n\n7. **Commute and Travel Updates**:\n   - Google Assistant provides real-time traffic updates, flight status, and other travel information to help you stay on schedule.\n\n8. **Visual Search and Actions**:\n   - With devices like Google Nest Hub, you can use visual input to search for information or control your device. For example, you can point at an item and ask Google to identify it or find similar products.\n\n9. **Integration with Third-Party Apps**:\n   - Google Assistant can integrate with a wide range of third-party apps, allowing you to perform tasks like sending messages, playing music, or ordering food using voice commands.\n\n10. **Proactive Suggestions**:\n    - Google Assistant can offer proactive suggestions based on your habits and calendar. For example, it might remind you to leave for an appointment or suggest a playlist based on your listening history.\n\n11. **Screen Contextual Awareness**:\n    - On devices with screens, Google Assistant can understand the context of what\u2019s on the screen. You can ask questions about information displayed in apps or websites.\n\n12. **Reminders and Lists**:\n    - You can easily create and manage reminders and shopping lists with voice commands, which sync across your devices.\n\nThese features make Google Assistant a versatile and powerful tool for managing your daily life, staying informed, and interacting with technology in a more intuitive way.",
